1. Introduction to Langchain why do we need langchain

Opensource framework used for developing applications using LLMs

A High overview system design for a application where we upload pdf and ask question from it.

  • First we do semantic search means we try to understand users query and then fetch the pages of the PDFs which is relevant according to the query.
  • now we merge users query and the pages to make system query.
  • and then we sent into the brain(LLMs) and it has to be contex aware text generation capablity

Semantic Search


flow of semantic search

  1. first we convert each paragraph(green one) to a vector database let say 100 dimension
  2. Now whenever the query asked we convert the query to same 100 dimension vector database then the find the similarity between each paragraph and query.
  3. the most similar paragraph is used to answer the query.

Detail Low level overview of the same above system


Summary
  • The workflow of build these type of application is so complex with lots of moving parts and if we want to change something then we have to buid from scratch.
  • that's where LangChain comes to the picture it tells that you only focus on main part of the technology i handle all the workflow
Abstract
  • Langchain has concept of chains where we can chain a series of events where one outpus goes into other inputs and we can change any chain which make the task much eaiser and reliable.
  • Model Agnostic Development (supports multiple components like you can change any model or change your clound services.)
  • Complete ecosystem
  • Memory and state handling we can store previous memory.
What can you build using LangChain
  • Conversational Chatbots
  • AI knowledge Assistants
  • AI agent
  • Workflow Automation
  • Summarization/Research Helpers
